284
00:16:26,453 --> 00:16:29,189
That was great.

285
00:16:29,256 --> 00:16:31,157
It's how we got Gene to sleep.

286
00:16:31,225 --> 00:16:32,625
Well, let's not wake him up.

287
00:16:35,596 --> 00:16:38,264
They played in the pool for four hours

288
00:16:38,332 --> 00:16:41,067
and bounced on the bed for another two.

289
00:16:41,135 --> 00:16:43,903
I think everybody's gonna sleep very well.

290
00:16:43,971 --> 00:16:46,472
I need you to come over at
7:00 tomorrow to watch Gene.

291
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:48,174
I'll get these two breakfast on the road.

292
00:16:48,242 --> 00:16:50,877
Okay. Bonne nuit, les animaux.

293
00:16:50,945 --> 00:16:52,679
- Good night.
- Good night.

294
00:16:52,746 --> 00:16:56,115
You said you didn't have any experience
and you're like Maria Von Trapp.

295
00:16:56,183 --> 00:16:57,917
Professionally,

296
00:16:57,985 --> 00:17:00,887
but I have four nieces and six nephews.

297
00:17:10,931 --> 00:17:13,800
Shh.

298
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:16,536
So how was your meeting?

299
00:17:16,604 --> 00:17:19,739
Pick me up and move me to my bed.

300
00:17:24,111 --> 00:17:26,012
Well, hello there.

301
00:17:28,549 --> 00:17:31,451
Stephanie, this is Sally and Bobby.

302
00:17:31,518 --> 00:17:33,186
- Hello.
- Hi.

303
00:17:33,254 --> 00:17:35,488
Well, it's very nice to meet you.

304
00:17:35,556 --> 00:17:38,124
How do you like California?

305
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:41,628
They love it.

306
00:17:41,695 --> 00:17:44,631
The notary is supposed to be
here at 10:00, but she's late.

307
00:17:44,698 --> 00:17:48,501
My mom put the papers in order
so all you have to do is sign

308
00:17:48,569 --> 00:17:50,403
and then you can go to Marineland.

309
00:17:51,905 --> 00:17:53,239
Who painted on the wall?

310
00:17:54,608 --> 00:17:57,410
My friend Anna. She used to live here.

311
00:17:57,478 --> 00:17:58,978
Stephanie is her niece.

312
00:18:00,314 --> 00:18:01,881
Who's Dick?

313
00:18:06,453 --> 00:18:07,820
Well...

314
00:18:09,657 --> 00:18:11,157
That's me.

315
00:18:13,994 --> 00:18:15,762
That's my nickname sometimes.

316
00:18:22,102 --> 00:18:23,836
Go out back and get us some lemons.

317
00:18:27,908 --> 00:18:30,109
They're adorable.

318
00:18:33,247 --> 00:18:35,748
- Is this it?
- My friend Charlie is gonna

319
00:18:35,816 --> 00:18:37,717
help me move the piano back to my mom's,

320
00:18:37,785 --> 00:18:41,788
and the rest of it goes
to St. Vincent de Paul.

321
00:18:41,855 --> 00:18:44,324
Four boxes. Good for her.

322
00:18:44,391 --> 00:18:47,694
Oh, she wanted
you to have something.

323
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,701
It's her engagement ring from Don.

324
00:18:56,437 --> 00:18:59,405
- Don't you want it?
- She wanted you to have it.

325
00:18:59,473 --> 00:19:01,307
You shouldn't play around with that.

326
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:03,543
Besides, I don't believe in it.

327
00:19:09,183 --> 00:19:10,683
So are you going back to school?

328
00:19:10,751 --> 00:19:12,285
Not for the moment.

329
00:19:12,353 --> 00:19:14,954
What are you gonna do?

330
00:19:15,022 --> 00:19:16,689
I don't know.

331
00:19:16,757 --> 00:19:18,691
That's the best part, right?

332
00:19:18,759 --> 00:19:20,560
Got the rest of my life ahead of me.

333
00:19:20,627 --> 00:19:21,828
So do you.

334
00:19:24,531 --> 00:19:25,698
Now that's her.

335
00:19:44,318 --> 00:19:45,618
Who's that?

336
00:19:46,954 --> 00:19:49,422
- How was it?
- Most of it was fun.

337
00:19:49,490 --> 00:19:52,325
- Daddy, are you coming in?
- I'm not wearing my bathing suit.

338
00:19:52,393 --> 00:19:53,826
Come in. You have to come in.

339
00:19:53,894 --> 00:19:56,362
- I want to be a shark.
- Come on, daddy.

340
00:19:58,665 --> 00:20:00,533
You swim all the time in New York.

341
00:20:00,601 --> 00:20:02,335
I'm really beat.

342
00:20:26,026 --> 00:20:29,195
Hey, should I throw
some herring to you two?

343
00:20:31,064 --> 00:20:33,299
Oh!

344
00:20:46,346 --> 00:20:50,149
Dumbo. Mad tea party.

345
00:20:50,217 --> 00:20:52,051
And Mr. Toad.

346
00:20:52,119 --> 00:20:53,619
Gene can't go on Mr. Toad.

347
00:20:53,687 --> 00:20:55,521
I'll get it.

348
00:20:55,589 --> 00:20:57,590
He can stay with Megan
while we go on the ride.

349
00:20:58,792 --> 00:21:00,293
Then Megan can't go.

350
00:21:03,230 --> 00:21:04,297
Hi, Sally.

351
00:21:05,966 --> 00:21:07,366
This is my friend Camille.

352
00:21:07,434 --> 00:21:10,903
Camille, this is Don,
Gene, Bobby and Sally.

353
00:21:10,971 --> 00:21:12,672
Hello, everybody.

354
00:21:12,739 --> 00:21:14,841
I just wanted to make sure you
didn't need anything else.

355
00:21:14,908 --> 00:21:16,476
No, I think we're okay.

356
00:21:17,911 --> 00:21:20,379
- Where are you going?
- The Whisky a Go Go.

357
00:21:20,447 --> 00:21:23,115
Well, good night, everybody.

358
00:21:23,183 --> 00:21:24,851
Good night. Have fun.

359
00:21:31,158 --> 00:21:32,859
What about Tomorrowland?

360
00:21:32,926 --> 00:21:34,427
I don't want to ride an elephant.

361
00:21:34,495 --> 00:21:36,295
I want to fly a jet.

362
00:21:39,851 --> 00:21:41,118
Hello.

363
00:21:41,185 --> 00:21:43,820
- Henry?
- I'm in here.

364
00:21:46,024 --> 00:21:48,859
I'm sorry. Everyone was late

365
00:21:48,927 --> 00:21:51,161
and then it took three of them to
light the pilot on the water heater.

366
00:21:51,229 --> 00:21:53,196
Carla called looking for you.

367
00:21:53,264 --> 00:21:55,966
Oh? And what did she want?

368
00:21:56,034 --> 00:21:58,402
You know what she wanted.

369
00:21:58,469 --> 00:22:00,370
You fired her and didn't tell me?

370
00:22:00,438 --> 00:22:02,539
Well, I am sorry.

371
00:22:02,607 --> 00:22:04,441
I didn't want her invoking your sympathies.

372
00:22:04,509 --> 00:22:07,778
- Why did you fire her?
- Because I don't trust her judgment.

373
00:22:07,845 --> 00:22:10,047
What did she say?

374
00:22:10,114 --> 00:22:12,783
She said you wouldn't give her
a letter of recommendation.

375
00:22:12,850 --> 00:22:14,518
How long did the woman work for you?

376
00:22:14,585 --> 00:22:16,787
I know she doesn't steal. What did she do?

377
00:22:16,854 --> 00:22:18,588
And don't tell me it's just
about the neighbor boy.

378
00:22:18,656 --> 00:22:20,724
Sally is not allowed to see him.

379
00:22:20,792 --> 00:22:23,226
- Carla said he's her friend.
- "Carla said"?

380
00:22:23,294 --> 00:22:25,929
- "Carla said"?!
- I don't understand what you're doing.

381
00:22:25,997 --> 00:22:28,999
You didn't want to move because you
wanted the kids to have some stability,

382
00:22:29,067 --> 00:22:31,134
and then you get rid of their
nanny since they were born?

383
00:22:31,202 --> 00:22:33,170
I wanted a fresh start, okay?

384
00:22:33,237 --> 00:22:35,973
- I'm entitled to that.
- There is no fresh start!

385
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:37,674
Lives carry on!

386
00:22:37,742 --> 00:22:41,111
Jesus, Henry.
Just once could you take my side?

387
00:22:41,179 --> 00:22:43,280
No one's ever on your side, Betty.

388
00:23:14,345 --> 00:23:15,679
Just a minute.

389
00:23:23,187 --> 00:23:24,721
Am I bothering you?

390
00:23:24,789 --> 00:23:26,890
No, I was out on the
balcony enjoying the view.

391
00:23:28,626 --> 00:23:32,262
I heard you come in and I wanted to go over

392
00:23:32,330 --> 00:23:35,632
the plan for tomorrow for Disneyland.

393
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:38,268
Do you think I should be involved
in such high-level decisions?

394
00:23:40,071 --> 00:23:41,972
Huh.

395
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:44,141
I can't turn on the TV.
They're asleep.

396
00:23:53,718 --> 00:23:55,986
There's nothing on TV.

397
00:23:56,054 --> 00:23:57,988
Come outside with me.

398
00:23:58,056 --> 00:23:59,523
It's so beautiful here.

399
00:24:01,325 --> 00:24:02,859
Did you have fun with your friend?

400
00:24:02,927 --> 00:24:05,362
Uh, not really.

401
00:24:05,430 --> 00:24:07,130
She's not really my friend.

402
00:24:07,198 --> 00:24:09,099
We just lived together during college.

403
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:12,002
My father's a professor.

404
00:24:12,036 --> 00:24:14,037
I think she liked him too much.

405
00:24:24,215 --> 00:24:26,016
So why did you see her?

406
00:24:27,885 --> 00:24:29,352
I don't know.

407
00:24:29,420 --> 00:24:31,721
She's an actress now.

408
00:24:31,789 --> 00:24:34,925
She's in two episodes of "Hogan's heroes."

409
00:24:34,992 --> 00:24:38,295
She told me I could never
do it because of my teeth.

410
00:24:38,362 --> 00:24:39,963
She actually said that to me.

411
00:24:41,933 --> 00:24:43,867
I don't even want to be an actress.

412
00:24:47,605 --> 00:24:49,372
I love your teeth.

413
00:24:51,442 --> 00:24:53,543
I took elocution lessons
when I moved to New York.

414
00:24:53,611 --> 00:24:56,346
The teacher said I had
the mouth of a singer.

415
00:25:12,396 --> 00:25:14,197
Are you sure we should do this?

416
00:25:15,633 --> 00:25:17,334
I've been thinking about you so much.

417
00:26:05,349 --> 00:26:07,817
Were you thinking about this
when I asked you to come?

418
00:26:11,489 --> 00:26:13,990
It was the first thought
that went through my head.

419
00:26:16,460 --> 00:26:18,361
I was gonna miss you so much, anyway.

420
00:26:20,398 --> 00:26:22,599
You don't know anything about me.

421
00:26:22,667 --> 00:26:24,534
But I do.

422
00:26:26,404 --> 00:26:28,238
I know that you have a good heart

423
00:26:28,306 --> 00:26:31,474
and I know that you're
always trying to be better.

424
00:26:33,110 --> 00:26:34,511
We all try.

425
00:26:35,947 --> 00:26:37,647
We don't always make it.

426
00:26:42,587 --> 00:26:44,287
I've done a lot of things.

427
00:26:46,724 --> 00:26:48,892
I know who you are now.

428
00:26:57,735 --> 00:26:59,736
It's getting light outside.

429
00:27:01,138 --> 00:27:03,673
I should get back before the sun comes up.

430
00:27:06,510 --> 00:27:07,978
They're little roosters.

431
00:27:12,016 --> 00:27:14,150
Then you should go.

432
00:27:14,218 --> 00:27:16,253
I don't want to confuse them.

433
00:27:26,897 --> 00:27:29,899
I want to know if I can knock on
this door again tomorrow night

434
00:27:29,967 --> 00:27:32,836
or if this is just what it is,

435
00:27:32,903 --> 00:27:34,437
like that night in the office.

436
00:27:35,973 --> 00:27:37,874
I need to know. I don't know why.

437
00:27:39,243 --> 00:27:40,944
Because you're afraid?

438
00:27:42,446 --> 00:27:45,015
You shouldn't be.

439
00:27:50,554 --> 00:27:52,989
Disneyland fireworks are at 9:00.

440
00:27:55,426 --> 00:27:58,628
How about dinner tomorrow night

441
00:27:58,696 --> 00:28:00,797
at 11:00 right here?

442
00:28:02,166 --> 00:28:04,167
We're gonna be together all day.

443
00:28:19,150 --> 00:28:22,085
This is Art.
Art, Ken Cosgrove and Patricia...

444
00:28:22,153 --> 00:28:24,054
- What was it?
- Peggy Olson.

445
00:28:24,121 --> 00:28:26,122
Sit. I'd offer you coffee,

446
00:28:26,190 --> 00:28:27,691
but everybody's gone for the holiday.

447
00:28:27,758 --> 00:28:29,359
The perils of being in charge.

448
00:28:31,662 --> 00:28:33,863
So you can tell we don't
have a lot of time.

449
00:28:33,931 --> 00:28:37,100
I mean not just today.
We're in kind of a bind.

450
00:28:37,168 --> 00:28:39,369
We're no worse than we were before,

451
00:28:39,437 --> 00:28:41,604
- and I hated those people.
- Do you have the old work?

452
00:28:41,672 --> 00:28:45,775
Somewhere. Look, it was a gorgeous girl...

453
00:28:45,843 --> 00:28:49,245
High heels, jewelry... Pulling
up this Cinderella gown

454
00:28:49,313 --> 00:28:51,014
to show the Topaz.

455
00:28:51,082 --> 00:28:53,616
But she wasn't Cinderella and
where the hell was she going?

456
00:28:53,684 --> 00:28:56,753
We want something that'll stand out.

457
00:28:56,821 --> 00:28:58,455
I don't care if it's a cartoon.

458
00:28:58,522 --> 00:29:00,390
I don't care if it's
Abe became wearing 'em.

459
00:29:00,458 --> 00:29:03,293
We're a tiny company.
We need to make a stink.

460
00:29:03,361 --> 00:29:06,429
Well, I've worn them but what qualities,

461
00:29:06,497 --> 00:29:08,898
in your mind, do they have
that make them unique?

462
00:29:08,966 --> 00:29:11,134
You're wearing them right now?

463
00:29:11,202 --> 00:29:14,771
Yes, because I can wear Topaz
pantyhose with anything.

464
00:29:14,839 --> 00:29:17,273
I'm wearing them at work right now

465
00:29:17,341 --> 00:29:20,143
and I'll change everything but
my hose before I go out tonight.

466
00:29:20,211 --> 00:29:22,679
One pair... That's all you need with Topaz.

467
00:29:24,548 --> 00:29:27,117
If we only sold each girl one
pair, we'd be out of business.

468
00:29:29,520 --> 00:29:33,123
"Topaz, the only pair of
pantyhose you'll ever need.

469
00:29:33,190 --> 00:29:35,358
Bad for business. Good for you."

470
00:29:36,627 --> 00:29:38,328
That's very funny,

471
00:29:38,396 --> 00:29:40,230
'cause it says our product's so good,

472
00:29:40,297 --> 00:29:42,732
we're not even interested in ourselves.

473
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:45,101
Okay, that's one. What else you got?

474
00:29:45,169 --> 00:29:47,837
Um, well,

475
00:29:47,905 --> 00:29:50,807
I'd have to think more,
but it might be great

476
00:29:50,875 --> 00:29:52,575
to show a bunch of different outfits...

477
00:29:52,643 --> 00:29:54,778
One for formal, one for business,

478
00:29:54,845 --> 00:29:57,514
one a little sporty...

479
00:29:57,581 --> 00:30:00,550
And something like

480
00:30:00,618 --> 00:30:02,919
"single pair, singular comfort."

481
00:30:02,987 --> 00:30:04,921
It's got the word "single" in it.

482
00:30:04,989 --> 00:30:06,656
That's two.

483
00:30:25,974 --> 00:30:29,576
Daddy, tell Sally that
snakes used to have legs.

484
00:30:29,644 --> 00:30:31,111
I don't know if that's true.

485
00:30:31,179 --> 00:30:32,579
You know it's true in the Bible.

486
00:30:32,647 --> 00:30:34,648
We learned that they used to be fish

487
00:30:34,716 --> 00:30:36,950
and he doesn't know because
he has baby science.

488
00:30:37,018 --> 00:30:39,853
- They found a skeleton.
- Where? You don't know.

489
00:30:39,921 --> 00:30:42,156
- You're a short stuff.
- Okay, "Thally."

490
00:30:42,223 --> 00:30:44,892
- Shut up!
- Great.

491
00:30:46,461 --> 00:30:49,096
Don't be upset. It's just a milkshake.

492
00:30:51,132 --> 00:30:53,500
Can you grab a straw or some napkins?
This is my last dress.

493
00:31:12,820 --> 00:31:16,423
I'm sorry. Is it late?

494
00:31:18,159 --> 00:31:20,194
I wanted to let you sleep.

495
00:31:21,429 --> 00:31:23,163
How long have you been up?

496
00:31:23,231 --> 00:31:25,732
- A few hours.
- What's wrong?

497
00:31:28,736 --> 00:31:30,237
I couldn't sleep.

498
00:31:31,906 --> 00:31:33,874
I just kept thinking about you.

499
00:31:35,210 --> 00:31:36,977
Well, I'm right here.

500
00:31:41,149 --> 00:31:43,750
I don't know what it is about you but...

501
00:31:45,553 --> 00:31:47,721
I feel like myself

502
00:31:47,789 --> 00:31:50,557
when I'm with you,

503
00:31:50,625 --> 00:31:53,093
but the way I always wanted to feel.

504
00:31:56,664 --> 00:31:59,800
Because I'm in love with you, Megan,

505
00:31:59,867 --> 00:32:01,835
and I think I have been for a while.

506
00:32:04,105 --> 00:32:05,539
Don.

507
00:32:09,577 --> 00:32:11,445
Oh my goodness.

508
00:32:13,014 --> 00:32:14,214
Open it.

509
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:21,455
It's beautiful.

510
00:32:23,157 --> 00:32:25,659
When I saw you sleeping there, I thought...

511
00:32:28,263 --> 00:32:31,265
I couldn't imagine not seeing
you there every morning.

512
00:32:34,836 --> 00:32:36,803
Will you marry me?

513
00:32:38,873 --> 00:32:40,507
Oh, I... I... I...

514
00:32:41,876 --> 00:32:43,944
I don't know what to say.

515
00:32:44,012 --> 00:32:46,079
This is all so fast.

516
00:32:46,147 --> 00:32:48,882
Did you ever think of the number of things

517
00:32:48,950 --> 00:32:51,752
that had to happen
for me to get to know you?

518
00:32:53,688 --> 00:32:54,988
But everything happened,

519
00:32:56,391 --> 00:32:58,258
and it got me here.

520
00:32:59,494 --> 00:33:01,061
What does that mean?

521
00:33:02,930 --> 00:33:04,665
I can't believe this.

522
00:33:06,167 --> 00:33:07,768
Yes. Yes.

523
00:33:20,315 --> 00:33:22,783
You have a ring? How long have
you been thinking about this?

524
00:33:22,850 --> 00:33:24,718
It's been in my family...

525
00:33:27,889 --> 00:33:29,856
Not my family, really.

526
00:33:31,793 --> 00:33:33,593
It belonged to someone
very important to me.

527
00:33:35,163 --> 00:33:37,130
I don't believe this.

528
00:33:37,198 --> 00:33:39,232
I have to call my mother.

529
00:33:39,300 --> 00:33:42,302
I had this feeling and I
called her from California

530
00:33:42,370 --> 00:33:44,838
- because I wanted it to go away.
- I saw it on the bill.

531
00:33:44,906 --> 00:33:47,274
Sorry.
I... I... I have to call her.

532
00:33:47,342 --> 00:33:48,809
Do you want me
to call her from work?

533
00:33:48,876 --> 00:33:51,578
No, call her.

534
00:33:51,646 --> 00:33:53,380
What about work? What do we do?

535
00:33:53,448 --> 00:33:55,682
We tell everybody.

536
00:33:55,750 --> 00:33:59,386
Oh. Okay.

537
00:34:03,791 --> 00:34:06,026
Do you want me to leave you alone?

538
00:34:06,094 --> 00:34:09,229
- Do you want me to talk to her?
- Oh. Do you speak French?

539
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:22,042
Maman, c'est moi. J'ai des nouvelles.

540
00:34:22,110 --> 00:34:24,344
Va chercher papa, vite.

541
00:34:26,013 --> 00:34:28,081
What the hell's going on?

542
00:34:28,149 --> 00:34:29,983
I don't know. He wouldn't say.

543
00:34:30,051 --> 00:34:32,285
Look, it's you... Brown as a Berry.

544
00:34:32,353 --> 00:34:34,287
- How was the coast?
- Wonderful.

545
00:34:34,355 --> 00:34:36,156
Joan, could you shut the door?

546
00:34:40,128 --> 00:34:41,928
I have an announcement to make

547
00:34:41,996 --> 00:34:43,830
and it shouldn't change anything here

548
00:34:43,898 --> 00:34:45,832
except for me and maybe for Joan.

549
00:34:45,900 --> 00:34:49,536
But Miss Calvet and I are getting married.

550
00:34:51,072 --> 00:34:53,807
- Who the hell's that?
- Megan.

551
00:34:53,875 --> 00:34:55,542
Really?

552
00:34:58,713 --> 00:35:01,448
Congratulations, Don.

553
00:35:01,516 --> 00:35:03,250
I wish you the best of luck.

554
00:35:04,419 --> 00:35:05,919
Megan out there?

555
00:35:05,987 --> 00:35:07,521
Yeah, I know it's a surprise,

556
00:35:07,588 --> 00:35:10,690
but she makes me very happy

557
00:35:10,758 --> 00:35:13,293
and, well...

558
00:35:13,361 --> 00:35:15,262
It's something we both want very much.

559
00:35:16,497 --> 00:35:17,531
Well, let's get her in here.

560
00:35:20,234 --> 00:35:21,368
Megan.

561
00:35:25,873 --> 00:35:27,841
- How exciting for you.
- I know.

562
00:35:27,909 --> 00:35:30,444
- I can't believe it.
- Congratulations, dear.

563
00:35:30,511 --> 00:35:32,679
You don't say "congratulations" to the bride.

564
00:35:32,747 --> 00:35:34,381
You say "best wishes."

565
00:35:34,449 --> 00:35:36,183
Congratulations, Don.

566
00:35:36,250 --> 00:35:38,652
Let's have a toast.
Megan, could you get us some ice?

567
00:35:40,021 --> 00:35:41,822
I'm teasing.

568
00:35:41,889 --> 00:35:43,890
See, Don? This is the way to behave.

569
00:35:45,893 --> 00:35:48,662
- So when are you getting married?
- I don't know.

570
00:35:48,729 --> 00:35:51,031
- We haven't discussed it.
- Soon.

571
00:35:52,200 --> 00:35:54,434
Art Garten just called.

572
00:35:54,502 --> 00:35:57,204
No. What did he say?

573
00:35:57,271 --> 00:36:00,106
He said he liked ideas two and
four and we've got a week.

574
00:36:00,174 --> 00:36:01,908
Ah!

575
00:36:05,213 --> 00:36:07,714
- Shall we go rub it in?
- After you.

576
00:36:07,782 --> 00:36:09,282
You did it.

577
00:36:13,287 --> 00:36:15,555
- We've got some great news.
- Are you two getting married?

578
00:36:20,495 --> 00:36:22,195
What's going on?

579
00:36:23,464 --> 00:36:25,165
They're getting married.

580
00:36:26,601 --> 00:36:29,135
- Really?
- Oh, congratulations.

581
00:36:29,203 --> 00:36:31,004
- Thank you.
- It's incredible.

582
00:36:31,072 --> 00:36:32,839
I know. It just happened.

583
00:36:32,907 --> 00:36:36,276
That's incredible. You must be so happy.

584
00:36:40,147 --> 00:36:42,182
Um, I'll get it.

585
00:36:45,086 --> 00:36:48,021
We have some news too. Peg.

586
00:36:48,089 --> 00:36:50,524
Yes, we signed an account...

587
00:36:50,591 --> 00:36:53,226
Topaz pantyhose.
It's a quarter of a million dollars.

588
00:36:53,294 --> 00:36:55,562
- How'd you do that?
- Peggy found out about them

589
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:57,030
and then we met over the holiday.

590
00:36:57,098 --> 00:36:59,699
That's great news. We broke the streak.

591
00:36:59,767 --> 00:37:03,036
What a great day. Good work, both of you.

592
00:37:03,104 --> 00:37:05,672
So anyway, I guess we should tell everybody.

593
00:37:05,740 --> 00:37:07,841
Topaz needs work this week.

594
00:37:07,909 --> 00:37:09,910
I hope you have all the happiness

595
00:37:09,977 --> 00:37:13,313
that Peggy and I had signing this account.

596
00:37:13,381 --> 00:37:15,015
I'll be there in a minute.

597
00:37:21,022 --> 00:37:22,756
Wow.

598
00:37:24,091 --> 00:37:25,959
It's been going on awhile,

599
00:37:26,027 --> 00:37:29,896
but I appreciate your concern.

600
00:37:29,964 --> 00:37:32,999
Well, then I'm happy for you...

601
00:37:33,067 --> 00:37:35,101
Both of you.

602
00:37:36,404 --> 00:37:38,471
She's very beautiful.

603
00:37:39,674 --> 00:37:41,308
You know she reminds me of you.

604
00:37:42,877 --> 00:37:44,511
She's got the same spark.

605
00:37:45,913 --> 00:37:48,515
I know she admires you
just as much as I do.

606
00:38:04,332 --> 00:38:05,899
It was Dr. Miller again.

607
00:38:08,235 --> 00:38:10,904
It's not gonna get any
easier the longer you wait.

608
00:38:16,744 --> 00:38:19,212
Whatever could be on your mind?

609
00:38:23,618 --> 00:38:25,485
Can you believe it?

610
00:38:25,553 --> 00:38:28,154
It happens all the time.

611
00:38:28,222 --> 00:38:30,657
They're all just between marriages.
You know that.

612
00:38:31,993 --> 00:38:33,994
He'll probably make her a copywriter.

613
00:38:34,061 --> 00:38:36,863
He's not going to want
to be married to his secretary.

614
00:38:36,931 --> 00:38:40,333
Really? Is that what he meant?

615
00:38:40,401 --> 00:38:43,003
"She admires you"?

616
00:38:43,070 --> 00:38:44,270
Jesus.

617
00:38:45,806 --> 00:38:48,008
That's the way it works for some.

618
00:38:49,543 --> 00:38:52,479
You know, I just saved this company.

619
00:38:52,546 --> 00:38:55,415
I signed the first new business
since Lucky Strike left,

620
00:38:55,483 --> 00:38:57,517
but it's not as important
as getting married.

621
00:38:57,585 --> 00:38:59,219
Again.

622
00:38:59,286 --> 00:39:02,756
Well, I was just made Director
of Agency Operations...

623
00:39:02,823 --> 00:39:05,425
A title, no money of course...

624
00:39:05,493 --> 00:39:07,427
And if they poured champagne,
it must've been

625
00:39:07,495 --> 00:39:09,195
while I was pushing the mail cart.

626
00:39:09,263 --> 00:39:11,297
A pretty face comes along

627
00:39:11,365 --> 00:39:12,899
and everything goes out the window.

628
00:39:12,967 --> 00:39:15,602
Well, I learned a long time ago

629
00:39:15,670 --> 00:39:18,204
to not get all my
satisfaction from this job.

630
00:39:20,174 --> 00:39:21,441
That's bullshit.

631
00:39:39,280 --> 00:39:41,581
- Faye Miller.
- Hi, it's me.

632
00:39:43,384 --> 00:39:45,552
I was starting to worry
you were ill or something.

633
00:39:46,787 --> 00:39:48,355
I need to talk to you.

634
00:39:48,422 --> 00:39:50,924
Well, I was gonna come by at lunch anyway.

635
00:39:50,992 --> 00:39:52,926
Oh, no, you shouldn't do that.

636
00:39:52,994 --> 00:39:54,361
Why don't we meet somewhere?

637
00:39:55,930 --> 00:39:57,464
What is going on?

638
00:39:59,233 --> 00:40:01,401
Something happened
and I'd like to talk to you

639
00:40:01,469 --> 00:40:03,136
about it face to face.

640
00:40:03,204 --> 00:40:04,771
Meet me for coffee.

641
00:40:05,940 --> 00:40:07,274
Okay.

642
00:40:10,077 --> 00:40:11,144
You know what?

643
00:40:11,212 --> 00:40:13,613
I'm not gonna have some conversation

644
00:40:13,681 --> 00:40:15,482
and have to sit through coffee afterwards.

645
00:40:16,651 --> 00:40:17,984
Just get to it.

646
00:40:25,192 --> 00:40:28,094
Well, I...

647
00:40:29,864 --> 00:40:31,331
Met somebody...

648
00:40:33,668 --> 00:40:36,569
And we're engaged.

649
00:40:36,637 --> 00:40:38,805
Are you kidding me?

650
00:40:38,873 --> 00:40:42,742
I know... I know, it's a surprise.
It was for me too.

651
00:40:43,878 --> 00:40:45,545
Jesus.

652
00:40:45,613 --> 00:40:47,247
Who is she?

653
00:40:48,549 --> 00:40:50,717
What's the difference?

654
00:40:50,785 --> 00:40:52,652
I fell in love.

655
00:40:54,021 --> 00:40:55,555
I didn't mean for this to happen.

656
00:40:55,623 --> 00:40:59,926
You've been very important to me.

657
00:41:01,262 --> 00:41:02,762
So you're not gonna put an ad

658
00:41:02,830 --> 00:41:05,031
in "The New York Times"
saying you never liked me?

659
00:41:05,099 --> 00:41:08,068
- Faye.
- Well, I hope you're very happy,

660
00:41:08,135 --> 00:41:11,504
and I hope she knows you only
like the beginnings of things.

661
00:41:13,307 --> 00:41:15,542
I'm sorry.

662
00:41:15,609 --> 00:41:17,477
I don't know what else to say.

663
00:41:17,545 --> 00:41:18,712
Goodbye.

664
00:41:33,494 --> 00:41:34,995
I saw the light go off.

665
00:41:36,330 --> 00:41:39,332
It's fine. It's done.

666
00:41:47,575 --> 00:41:49,442
I love you, you know.

667
00:42:02,923 --> 00:42:04,391
And he's smiling like a fool,

668
00:42:04,458 --> 00:42:06,760
like he's the first man that
ever married his secretary.

669
00:42:06,827 --> 00:42:09,396
She's 25, as if that's news.

670
00:42:09,463 --> 00:42:11,464
So when are you going
to tell them your news?

671
00:42:11,532 --> 00:42:13,466
They'll know soon enough.

672
00:42:13,534 --> 00:42:16,770
Are you showing at all?
The picture I have of you doesn't change.

673
00:42:16,837 --> 00:42:19,639
I'll take a new one and I'll send it to you.

674
00:42:19,707 --> 00:42:22,042
You know all I want to know.

675
00:42:22,109 --> 00:42:25,378
Yes, honey, they're bigger.

676
00:42:25,446 --> 00:42:27,981
Oh! Why are you torturing me?

677
00:42:28,049 --> 00:42:30,183
I just woke up and it's already 90° here.

678
00:42:31,752 --> 00:42:33,853
Listen, I've gotta go.

679
00:42:33,921 --> 00:42:36,156
- Not yet.
- What?

680
00:42:36,223 --> 00:42:38,358
Not yet.

681
00:42:38,426 --> 00:42:41,895
Now you listen to the doctor. You have to eat.
Don't worry about your figure.

682
00:42:41,962 --> 00:42:43,997
I'll whip you and the baby
into shape when I get back.

683
00:42:44,065 --> 00:42:45,732
Okay.

684
00:42:47,201 --> 00:42:49,135
I'll call you Thursday night your time.

685
00:42:49,203 --> 00:42:52,238
Okay. I love you.

686
00:42:52,306 --> 00:42:54,074
I love you too.

687
00:43:17,698 --> 00:43:20,667
Hello?

688
00:43:20,734 --> 00:43:23,570
Mrs. Truxton?

689
00:43:23,637 --> 00:43:25,605
No, it's me.

690
00:43:27,508 --> 00:43:30,710
- What are you doing here?
- It's Tuesday at 7:00.

691
00:43:30,778 --> 00:43:32,912
I thought I told you I had a listing
appointment with the real estate agent.

692
00:43:35,316 --> 00:43:37,317
Oh, I didn't realize that was today.

693
00:43:37,384 --> 00:43:40,820
I forgot about the cabinets
in the guest bath.

694
00:43:40,888 --> 00:43:42,489
So you weren't that thorough?

695
00:43:42,556 --> 00:43:44,290
I guess not.

696
00:43:53,134 --> 00:43:54,868
Ah.

697
00:44:10,084 --> 00:44:13,186
Do you like the new house?

698
00:44:13,254 --> 00:44:16,389
I do. It's got a lot of character.

699
00:44:17,725 --> 00:44:19,526
I'll probably have to tear out the kitchen.

700
00:44:23,597 --> 00:44:25,231
Remember this place?

701
00:44:27,334 --> 00:44:28,935
I do.

702
00:44:31,071 --> 00:44:32,805
It's different. That's for certain.

703
00:44:34,341 --> 00:44:35,842
Isn't that what you wanted?

704
00:44:37,011 --> 00:44:38,878
I don't know, Don.

705
00:44:43,217 --> 00:44:45,084
Things aren't perfect.

706
00:44:47,521 --> 00:44:49,656
So you'll move again.

707
00:44:55,529 --> 00:44:57,263
So much changes

708
00:44:57,331 --> 00:44:59,065
it's made everything...

709
00:45:00,701 --> 00:45:02,101
Difficult.

710
00:45:08,309 --> 00:45:10,276
I have to tell you something.

711
00:45:13,514 --> 00:45:15,048
I met someone.

712
00:45:18,185 --> 00:45:19,686
I'm engaged.

713
00:45:22,122 --> 00:45:23,756
Really?

714
00:45:27,561 --> 00:45:29,128
Bethany Van Nuys?

715
00:45:29,196 --> 00:45:32,232
No. Someone at work.

716
00:45:33,534 --> 00:45:34,968
Oh.

717
00:45:47,014 --> 00:45:48,982
I'm very happy for you.

718
00:45:51,719 --> 00:45:53,386
It's okay, Betty.

719
00:45:56,523 --> 00:45:58,491
I don't know why I'm surprised.

720
00:46:01,862 --> 00:46:04,597
Is she your secretary?
I know she watched the kids in California.

721
00:46:04,665 --> 00:46:05,932
Yes.

722
00:46:12,072 --> 00:46:15,041
So I will see you the weekend after next.
What is that, the 23rd?

723
00:46:15,109 --> 00:46:16,542
I think so.

724
00:46:18,612 --> 00:46:20,013
Wait.

725
00:46:31,025 --> 00:46:33,493
Congratulations.

726
00:46:33,560 --> 00:46:35,461
Thank you.

